@NODE ReadMe "Read Me"


                              Back Door V2.81

                                Compiled By:
                             Stephen Birmingham
                                  03/09/94


 WELCOME:

 Welcome to Back Door @{" V2.81 " Link VersionHistory} (the ultimate cheaters guide).
 Yes, as you've probibly guesed by now it's a database full of level
 codes, cheat modes and playing tips etc.  Not another one I here you cry.
 Well, the difference between this one and the many others available is
 that this contains some of the most recently released cheats modes
 available.  There are even some cheats in this database that have never
 been printed before, Just have a look for yourself.
 Any how, most of the other databases are just growing old and collecting
 dust having not been updated for some time.  This however, will not be
 the case with back door.


 DATA:

 To save confusion all the cheat modes/codes are in capital letters and
 are in `quotes'.
 Some of the codes/cheats in this file have harsh and abusive language,
 but don't worry, you will be well warned when this is the case.


 BABBLE:

 Back Door is public domain so please spread it around as much possible.
 I have included the latest version of D-Copy on this disk for you to do
 this.  To gain access to D-Copy just quit this database and workbench
 will then load.

                                                        Stephen Birmingham


@ENDNODE

@NODE VersionHistory "Version History"


 V1.00  - Game Cheats as it was originaly titled was just a small
          collection of cheat modes which was configured around the text
          reader PPMore by Nico François.

 V1.XX  - Version history to long, cut to V2.00.

 V2.00  - Converted file to be viewed through MultiGuide from CBM.
          Changed database name to Back Door, also the version number now
          represents the number of games covered in the database.

 V2.22t - Back Door now viewed through PPGuide. Contains codes, cheats and
          tips for over 200 games. First public release (test version).

 V2.81  - Various cheat modes added and some stand corrected. New Layout.


@ENDNODE

