@NODE Help "Help"


 MENUS:

 The Main Menu is quite simple to understand. If you are searching for a
 specific game title for which you want help with then you can either
 click on the Index button which can be found on the second title bar or
 click on the approriate alphabet gadget. If you choose to click one of
 the alphabet gadgets then a second menu will appear listing all the
 games covered for that letter. If the game you want help with is not
 listed then you can Retrace back to the main menu. However, if it is
 listed then clicking on it will bring what information I have gathered
 for that game, e.g. level codes, cheat modes etc.


 DATA:

 If for some unknown reason you are having trouble correctly operating a
 cheat mode it could be because:

 A: If a cheat mode is in capitals then try it in lowercase and vice
 versa.  Also, if you have been told to type it in on the title screen
 try it on the high score table, during play or even when the game is
 paused.  I think you get the general idea.

 B: In the version of the game you have the cheat mode has been altered.
 This is often the case when a game is rereleased on a budget label etc.

 C: The source just may be incorrect.  I useualy do wait for confirmation
 of cheat modes/level codes etc before entering them into the database.
 However, because I can't test all the information out for myself, their
 is bound to be some incorrect data in this file.
 If you know this to be the case then I would appreciate you getting in
 touch and letting me know.


@ENDNODE

@NODE A.P.B. "A.P.B."


 Cheat Mode:

 Pressing up on the joystick and fire at the same time to start a new game
 enables you to start on any day up to day 16. Also, entering `ALF' into
 the high score table as your name give you infinite demerits.


@ENDNODE

@NODE A-Train "A-Train"


 Cheat Mode:

 Press [Caps-Lock] and type in `CHEATERCHEATERWIMP'.
 After two seconds your funds go up by $1 million and all the land you
 own is filled with building blocks.
 You can repeat this as many times as you like.


@ENDNODE

@NODE ActionFighter "Action Fighter"


 Cheat Mode:

 Once you've acheived a high score enter your name in as `ZBACKDOOR'.
 This will give you infinite lives and energy.


@ENDNODE

@NODE AddamsFamily-The "Addams Family - The"


 Level Codes:

 Pugsley      - V121B
 Granny       - V&YKW
 Wednesday    - VD2RL
 Fester       - VL#R4
 1st power-up - &1#1F
 2nd power-up - ?1S1M
 3rd power-up - BLSRS

 For Morticia, use the 3rd power-up code, go to the piano room and wait
 for the Addams Family music to play. Now open the self sealed door and
 finish the last level.


 Cheat Mode:

 Enter the code `11111' on the password screen for 100 lives.
 However, this cheat code was removed in later versions of the game.


 Playing Tips:

 In the hallway, go to the bottom left and press up on the joystick to
 reveal a hidden door. Now enter the door and on the next screen, directly
 above you is another hidden door which hides even more doors and extra
 lives. 
 Pause the game by pressing the [Spacebar] and then hit the [Escape] key.
 You will now be in a room with a continue door and a eacape door.
 Instead of choosing one of these options just keep walking left untill
 you come across another room full of extra lives.


@ENDNODE

