@NODE F/A-18Interceptor "F/A-18 Interceptor"


 Playing Tips:

 Select option 2 "Free Flight, No Enemy Confrontation" from the Main Menu.
 Then select zero instead of 1 to 4. The screen will go into a spiral
 and scroll way south to 34 by 117 degrees, placing your plane somewhere
 without a runway. This happens to be in the middle of Edwards Air Force
 Base, where the F/A-18 was flight tested. To take off you have to use the
 afterburners. 117 degrees is the furthest south you'll be able to fly,
 but you can go in other directions.


@ENDNODE

@NODE F-15StrikeEagle2 "F-15 Strike Eagle 2"


 Cheat Mode:

 To replenish your ammo supply simply press [Ctrl], [Alt] and [R] all at
 the same time.


@ENDNODE

@NODE F-29Retaliator "F-29 Retaliator"


 Cheat Mode:

 On the enlisting screen, enter your name as `THE DIDY MEN' but don't
 press the [Return] key. Now, click on the Colonel icon, press [Return]
 and select a battle area. Choose and accept a mission and start playing
 the game as you normally would. Now you can activate an automatic landing
 sequence by pressing the [Enter] on the numeric keypad.
 Also, on enrollment enter your name in as `CIARAN' then load up the
 pilots log. The name should now read Ocean OK. Now you can play any
 mission with the huge benefit of infinite missiles and cannons.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Falcon "Falcon"


 Cheat Mode:

 During play press [Ctrl], [Shift] and [X] simultaneously for increased
 afterburners, eight sidewinder missiles and a full magazine.


@ENDNODE

