@NODE Microcosm-CDł˛ "Microcosm - CDł˛"


 Cheat Mode:

 This cheat mode is a bit complicated, but if done correctly will give you
 infinite shields and all weapon systems.
 First pause the game and press any coloured button. You should hear
 either a high or a low beep. If you get a high beep then you've got the
 first digit of the code right. If you get a low beep it's wrong and you
 must start again from the first digit.
 It's just a question of elimination, say you press the red button and get
 a high beeb and then press the yellow button and get a low beeb then just
 start again making sure you press any other coloured button except yellow
 after the first red one, and so on.
 A weird noise tells you the cheat is active, unfortunately the cheat also
 sucks all the colour from the cut scenes.
 The code changes every time you start a new game. 


@ENDNODE

@NODE Monopoly "Monopoly"


 Cheat Mode:

 When someone doesn't want a property and it goes up for auction, keep
 pressing the left mouse button as fast as you can, and the other players
 can't bid for it. This means that you can get all of the properties for
 just Ł10.


@ENDNODE

@NODE MontyPythonsFlyingCircus "Monty Pythons Flying Circus"


